HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 756
By Baum
A RESOLUTION to recognize Nancy Garner on the occasion of
her retirement.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should recognize
those esteemed Tennesseans who have devoted their careers to strengthening our State's
institutions of higher learning and supporting the success of students, faculty, and programs
across Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, Nancy Garner is one such exemplary individual, who has served Middle
Tennessee State University (MTSU) with unwavering dedication, professionalism, and integrity
throughout her extraordinary fifty-year tenure, which includes decades of service as an
executive assistant in the Military Science Department; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Garner will be taking a much-deserved retirement on September 30,
2026; and
WHEREAS, Nancy Garner began her service at MTSU on September 1, 1976,
embarking on a career marked by exceptional commitment to the university's mission and to the
countless students, faculty, and staff whose lives she has touched; and
WHEREAS, since February 16, 1981, Ms. Garner has served as an executive assistant
in the Military Science Department, where her organizational expertise, deep institutional
knowledge, and steadfast support have been instrumental to the success of the department and
the Army Reserve Officers' Training Corps program at MTSU; and
WHEREAS, widely respected by colleagues, cadets, and university leadership alike,
Nancy Garner is known for her reliability, kindness, and tireless work ethic, consistently going
above and beyond to ensure the smooth operation of departmental activities and the success of
those she served; and
HJR0756
011138
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Ms. Garner's contributions have strengthened the Military Science
Department's ability to prepare future leaders for service to our State and nation, and her legacy
will continue to be felt long after her retirement; and
WHEREAS, throughout her remarkable career, Nancy Garner has exemplified the
highest ideals of public service, earning the admiration and gratitude of the entire MTSU
community; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Garner's distinguished career stands as a testament to the enduring
impact of committed public servants who devote their lives to supporting education and
developing future generations of leaders; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Nancy Garner for her fifty years of outstanding
service to Middle Tennessee State University and extend to her our best wishes for a happy and
fulfilling retirement and every continued success in her future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
